{"id":"witness","term":"Witness","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>More than one witness was required in criminal cases (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 17:6\">Deut. 17:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 19:15\">19:15</a>). They were the first to execute the sentence on the condemned (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 13:9\">Deut. 13:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 17:7\">17:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 21:13\">1 Kings 21:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 27:1\">Matt. 27:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 7:57\">Acts 7:57</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 7:58\">58</a>). False witnesses were liable to punishment (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 19:16\">Deut. 19:16-21</a>). It was also an offence to refuse to bear witness (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 5:1\">Lev. 5:1</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Deuteronomy 17:6","Deuteronomy 19:15","Deuteronomy 13:9","Deuteronomy 17:7","1 Kings 21:13","Matthew 27:1","Acts 7:57","Acts 7:58","Deuteronomy 19:16","Leviticus 5:1"]}